------------------------------------------------------------------------- INHERITANCE ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1Ô∏è‚É£ What is Inheritance ?
it is one of the priciple of oops,Inheritance is an OOP principle where a subclass inherits variables and methods from a superclass, 
creating an IS-A relationship and enabling code reusability.
üîπ Important clarity :
  - Child class values ko inherit nahi karta, sirf variables & methods inherit karta hai.
  - Parent object me p.age = 17 set karne se child ke object me value nahi aayegi.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Terminology
        - Child ‚Üí Parent
        - Subclass ‚Üí Superclass
        - Derived class ‚Üí Base class
note:- jab child bol rhe ho to parent bolo  and jab derived class bol rhe ho to base class bolo or jab subclass bol rhe ho to super class bolo.

3Ô∏è‚É£ IS-A Relationship Example:
     - Inheritance IS-A relationship hoti hai.
     - eg:-Dog is-a Animal.
     - Child class parent ke type ka hota hai.

üî∑ Why?
‚úî Code reusability
‚úî Avoid duplication
‚úî Easy maintenance
‚úî Supports polymorphism
‚úî Extends functionality of existing class


üî∑ Types of Inheritance :
| Type         | Description                            | Supported in Java?                                              | Example                                              |
| ------------ | -------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| Single       | 1 parent ‚Üí 1 child                     | ‚úî Supported                                                     | Animal ‚Üí Dog                                         |
| Multilevel   | Parent ‚Üí Child ‚Üí Grandchild            | ‚úî Supported                                                     | Animal ‚Üí Dog ‚Üí Puppy                                 |
| Hierarchical | One parent, many children              | ‚úî Supported                                                     | Animal ‚Üí Dog, Cat                                    |
| Multiple     | 1 child inherits from multiple parents | ‚ùå **Class level not allowed**‚úî Allowed using **interfaces**    |class C extends A,B ‚ùå<br>class C implements I1, I2 ‚úî|
| Hybrid       | Combination of two or more types of inheritance  | single + multilevel + hierarchical  (generally interfaces ke throurh hota h ‚ùå Class level not allowed       |


5Ô∏è‚É£ Diamond Problem ?
- jab ek child multiple parents ko inherit krega(technically java me possible nhi h) or dono parent me ek common method hoga to child class ke liye diamond problem create krega 
  isko avoid krne ke liye interface ka use hota hai.
- Interfaces me solution: Default method + override rule.
Note:- 
6Ô∏è‚É£ Object Class Inheritance (Implicit) :
                              - ‚úî Every class automatically extends Object.
                              - Java by default single inheritance follow karta hai.

7Ô∏è‚É£ Constructor Behavior in Inheritance / Constructor Rules :
    - Jab child ka object banta hai:
                          - Parent constructor pehle
                          - Child constructor baad me
                          - Order: Top ‚Üí Down

ANALYSIS CASE-1:
A()
